#: ../../../usage/index.md:60
msgid "Web Workers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:62
msgid ""
"By default, WebAssembly runs in the main browser thread, and it can make UI "
"non-responsive for long-running computations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:65
msgid ""
"To avoid this situation, one solution is to run {ref}`Pyodide in a WebWorker "
"<using_from_webworker>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:68
msgid ""
"It's also possible to run {ref}`Pyodide in a Service Worker "
"<using_from_service_worker>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:70
msgid ""
"If you're not sure whether you need web workers or service workers, here's "
"an [overview and comparison of the two](https://web.dev/workers-overview/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:73
msgid "Node.js"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:76
msgid ""
"Starting with Pyodide 0.25.0, Node.js < 18 is no longer officially "
"supported. Older versions of Node.js might still work, but they are not "
"tested or guaranteed to work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:80
msgid ""
"It is possible to install the [Pyodide npm package](https://www.npmjs.com/"
"package/pyodide) in Node.js."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:83
msgid "$ npm install pyodide\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:87
msgid "Once installed, you can run the following simple script:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:89
msgid ""
"// hello_python.mjs\n"
"import { loadPyodide } from \"pyodide\";\n"
"\n"
"async function hello_python() {\n"
"  let pyodide = await loadPyodide();\n"
"  return pyodide.runPythonAsync(\"1+1\");\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"const result = await hello_python();\n"
"console.log(\"Python says that 1+1 =\", result);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:102
msgid ""
"$ node hello_python.mjs\n"
"Python says that 1+1= 2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:107
msgid ""
"Or you can use the REPL. To start the Node.js REPL with support for top "
"level await, use `node --experimental-repl-await`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/index.md:110
msgid ""
"$ node --experimental-repl-await\n"
"Welcome to Node.js v18.5.0.\n"
"Type \".help\" for more information.\n"
"> const { loadPyodide } = await import(\"pyodide\");\n"
"undefined\n"
"> let pyodide = await loadPyodide();\n"
"undefined\n"
"> await pyodide.runPythonAsync(\"1+1\");\n"
"2\n"
msgstr ""
